   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"nbformat\": 4,\n",
    " \"nbformat_minor\": 5,\n",
    " \"metadata\": {\n",
    "  \"kernelspec\": {\n",
    "   \"display_name\": \"Python 3\",\n",
    "   \"language\": \"python\",\n",
    "   \"name\": \"python3\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  \"language_info\": {\n",
    "   \"name\": \"python\",\n",
    "   \"version\": \"3.11.0\"\n",
    "  }\n",
    " },\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"01-title\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# SpinachLang × IBM Quantum Simulator Demo\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"> **SpinachLang** is a quantum programming language that compiles `.sph` source to\\n\",\n",
    "    \"> multiple quantum backends via [PyTKET](https://cqcl.github.io/tket/pytket/api/).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"> This notebook walks the full pipeline:\\n\",\n",
    "    \">\\n\",\n",
    "    \"> ```\\n\",\n",
    "    \"> .sph source\\n\",\n",
    "    \">   ↓  spinachlang.to_tket_circuit()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"> pytket.Circuit  (native TKET IR)\\n\",\n",
    "    \">   ↓  spinachlang.to_qiskit_circuit()  [via pytket-qiskit]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"> qiskit.QuantumCircuit\\n\",\n",
    "    \">   ↓  qiskit_aer.AerSimulator  (IBM Quantum local simulator)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"> Counts / State-vectors / Visualizations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"> ```\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Demos in this notebook\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| # | Circuit | Key concept |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"|---|---------|-------------|\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| 1 | Single-qubit superposition | Hadamard gate, Bloch sphere |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| 2 | Bell state (2-qubit entanglement) | CNOT gate, Q-sphere |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| 3 | GHZ state (3-qubit entanglement) | Multi-qubit correlation |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| 4 | Deutsch's algorithm | Quantum oracle, phase kickback |\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"02-imports\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import textwrap\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# ── SpinachLang API ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from spinachlang import to_tket_circuit, to_qiskit_circuit\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# ── IBM Quantum / Qiskit ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from qiskit_aer import AerSimulator\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from qiskit.visualization import (\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    plot_histogram,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    plot_bloch_multivector,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    plot_state_qsphere,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    plot_state_city,\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from qiskit.quantum_info import Statevector\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# ── PyTKET interactive circuit viewer (optional) ──────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    from pytket.circuit.display import render_circuit_jupyter\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    _HAS_TKET_DISPLAY = True\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    _HAS_TKET_DISPLAY = False\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# ── Shared simulator instance ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"simulator = AerSimulator()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# ── Helpers ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"def show_tket_circuit(tket_circuit):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"Render a TKET circuit: use the interactive HTML viewer when available,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    otherwise print a textual summary of each gate command.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if _HAS_TKET_DISPLAY:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        return render_circuit_jupyter(tket_circuit)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"TKET circuit  ({tket_circuit.n_qubits} qubits, \\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"          f\\\"{tket_circuit.n_bits} classical bits, \\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"          f\\\"depth {tket_circuit.depth()})\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for cmd in tket_circuit.get_commands():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        print(f\\\"  {cmd}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"def run_shots(qiskit_circuit, shots: int = 2048, title: str = \\\"\\\"):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"Run a Qiskit circuit on AerSimulator and return a histogram plot.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    job    = simulator.run(qiskit_circuit, shots=shots)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    counts = job.result().get_counts()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    fig    = plot_histogram(counts, title=title or \\\"Measurement outcomes\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                            figsize=(7, 4), color=\\\"#4CAF50\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    return fig, counts\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"def statevector_from(spinach_code: str):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"Return a Qiskit Statevector for spinach code that has NO measurements.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    qc = to_qiskit_circuit(spinach_code)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    return Statevector.from_instruction(qc)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import qiskit, qiskit_aer, spinachlang  # version check\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"✅ All imports successful!\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"   Qiskit      : {qiskit.__version__}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"   Qiskit-Aer  : {qiskit_aer.__version__}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"03-syntax\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Spinach Language — Quick Reference\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```spinach\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# ── Qubit / classical-bit declarations ───────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"alice : q 0          # qubit at register index 0  →  Qubit(\\\"q\\\", 0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"flag  : b 0          # classical bit              →  Bit(\\\"c\\\", 0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# ── Apply a gate ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"alice -> H           # Hadamard on alice\\n\",\n",
    "    \"0     -> H           # Hadamard on qubit index 0 (shorthand)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"q 0   -> H           # same, explicit register syntax\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# ── Gate pipelines ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"alice -> H | M       # Hadamard then Measure\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# ── Two-qubit gates ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# FCX(arg): the *acted-on* qubit is the CONTROL, arg is the TARGET\\n\",\n",
    "    \"alice -> H | FCX(q 1)   # Bell pair: alice = control, q[1] = target\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# CX(arg):  arg is the CONTROL, acted-on qubit is the TARGET\\n\",\n",
    "    \"q 1   -> CX(alice)      # same wiring: alice = control, q[1] = target\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# ── Wildcard & list targets ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* -> M               # measure ALL qubits\\n\",\n",
    "    \"[alice, q 1] -> H    # apply H to a list\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# ── Conditional ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"q 0 -> X if flag     # classically conditioned gate\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"04-sec1-header\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## 1  ·  Single-Qubit Superposition\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"A single Hadamard gate transforms |0⟩ into an equal superposition:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"$$|0\\\\rangle \\\\xrightarrow{H} \\\\frac{|0\\\\rangle + |1\\\\rangle}{\\\\sqrt{2}}$$\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This is the simplest non-trivial quantum state — the qubit is *simultaneously* 0 and 1\\n\",\n",
    "    \"until observed.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"05-superpos-circuit\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ── 1a. Spinach source ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"SPH_SUPERPOS      = \\\"0 -> H\\\"        # for state-vector (no measurement)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"SPH_SUPERPOS_MEAS = \\\"0 -> H | M\\\"    # for shot simulation\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Spinach source (with measurement):\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(textwrap.indent(SPH_SUPERPOS_MEAS, \\\"  \\\"))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# ── 1b. PyTKET circuit ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"tket_superpos = to_tket_circuit(SPH_SUPERPOS_MEAS)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\nPyTKET circuit:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"show_tket_circuit(tket_superpos)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"06-superpos-draw\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ── 1c. Qiskit circuit diagram ────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"qc_superpos_meas = to_qiskit_circuit(SPH_SUPERPOS_MEAS)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Qiskit QuantumCircuit:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"qc_superpos_meas.draw('mpl', style='iqp', fold=-1)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"07-superpos-bloch\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ── 1d. Bloch sphere — state vector BEFORE measurement ────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# The |+⟩ state sits on the equator of the Bloch sphere at the +X pole.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sv_superpos = statevector_from(SPH_SUPERPOS)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"State vector: {sv_superpos}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig = plot_bloch_multivector(sv_superpos, title=\\\"Superposition |+⟩\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"08-superpos-shots\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ── 1e. Shot simulation — 50/50 histogram ─────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, counts = run_shots(qc_superpos_meas, shots=2048,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                        title=\\\"Superposition: 2048 shots\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Counts:\\\", counts)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"total = sum(counts.values())\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for state, n in sorted(counts.items()):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"  |{state}⟩  {n:5d} / {total}  ({100 * n / total:.1f}%)\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"09-sec2-header\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## 2  ·  Bell State (Two-Qubit Entanglement)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The Bell state $|\\\\Phi^+\\\\rangle$ is the archetypal entangled state:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"$$|\\\\Phi^+\\\\rangle = \\\\frac{|00\\\\rangle + |11\\\\rangle}{\\\\sqrt{2}}$$\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Circuit**: apply H to qubit 0, then a controlled-NOT (CNOT) with qubit 0 as control\\n\",\n",
    "    \"and qubit 1 as target.  In SpinachLang the `FCX` gate applies to the **control** qubit\\n\",\n",
    "    \"and takes the **target** as argument:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```spinach\\n\",\n",
    "    \"q 0 -> H | FCX(q 1)   # q0 = control, q1 = target\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* -> M\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"10-bell-circuit\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ── 2a. Spinach source ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"SPH_BELL      = \\\"q 0 -> H | FCX(q 1)\\\"          # no measurement  → state-vector\\n\",\n",
    "    \"SPH_BELL_MEAS = \\\"q 0 -> H | FCX(q 1)\\\\n* -> M\\\"  # with measurement → shots\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Spinach source (with measurement):\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(textwrap.indent(SPH_BELL_MEAS, \\\"  \\\"))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"tket_bell = to_tket_circuit(SPH_BELL_MEAS)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\nPyTKET circuit:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"show_tket_circuit(tket_bell)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"11-bell-draw\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ── 2b. Qiskit circuit diagram ────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"qc_bell_meas = to_qiskit_circuit(SPH_BELL_MEAS)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"qc_bell_meas.draw('mpl', style='iqp', fold=-1)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"12-bell-qsphere\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ── 2c. Q-sphere — entangled state before measurement ────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# The Bell state has equal amplitudes at |00⟩ and |11⟩ (north and south poles).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sv_bell = statevector_from(SPH_BELL)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"State vector amplitudes:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for basis, amp in zip([\\\"00\\\", \\\"01\\\", \\\"10\\\", \\\"11\\\"], sv_bell.data):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if abs(amp) > 1e-9:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        print(f\\\"  |{basis}⟩  amp = {amp:.4f}  prob = {abs(amp)**2:.4f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig = plot_state_qsphere(sv_bell, title=\\\"Bell state |Φ+⟩\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"13-bell-shots\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ── 2d. Shot simulation — only |00⟩ and |11⟩ ever appear ────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, counts = run_shots(qc_bell_meas, shots=2048,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                        title=\\\"Bell state |Φ+⟩: 2048 shots\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Counts:\\\", counts)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Entanglement signature: |01⟩ and |10⟩ should be absent.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"assert \\\"01\\\" not in counts and \\\"10\\\" not in counts, \\\\\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Unexpected mixed-state outcomes — entanglement broken!\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"✅ Only |00⟩ and |11⟩ observed — entanglement confirmed.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"14-sec3-header\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## 3  ·  GHZ State (Three-Qubit Entanglement)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The Greenberger–Horne–Zeilinger (GHZ) state extends Bell entanglement to three qubits:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"$$|\\\\text{GHZ}\\\\rangle = \\\\frac{|000\\\\rangle + |111\\\\rangle}{\\\\sqrt{2}}$$\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Circuit**: H on qubit 0, then chain two CNOTs: 0→1 and 0→2.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```spinach\\n\",\n",
    "    \"q 0 -> H | FCX(q 1) | FCX(q 2)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* -> M\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"15-ghz-circuit\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ── 3a. Spinach source ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"SPH_GHZ      = \\\"q 0 -> H | FCX(q 1) | FCX(q 2)\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"SPH_GHZ_MEAS = SPH_GHZ + \\\"\\\\n* -> M\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Spinach source:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(textwrap.indent(SPH_GHZ_MEAS, \\\"  \\\"))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"tket_ghz = to_tket_circuit(SPH_GHZ_MEAS)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\nPyTKET circuit:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"show_tket_circuit(tket_ghz)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"16-ghz-draw\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ── 3b. Qiskit circuit diagram ────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"qc_ghz_meas = to_qiskit_circuit(SPH_GHZ_MEAS)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"qc_ghz_meas.draw('mpl', style='iqp', fold=-1)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"17-ghz-statecity\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ── 3c. State-city plot — amplitudes before measurement ──────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sv_ghz = statevector_from(SPH_GHZ)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Non-zero amplitudes:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"basis_labels = [f\\\"{i:03b}\\\" for i in range(8)]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for label, amp in zip(basis_labels, sv_ghz.data):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if abs(amp) > 1e-9:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        print(f\\\"  |{label}⟩  {amp:.4f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig = plot_state_city(sv_ghz, title=\\\"GHZ state amplitudes\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                     figsize=(8, 5), alpha=0.6,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                     color=[\\\"#4CAF50\\\", \\\"#2196F3\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"18-ghz-shots\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ── 3d. Shot simulation — only |000⟩ and |111⟩ ───────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, counts = run_shots(qc_ghz_meas, shots=2048,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                        title=\\\"GHZ state: 2048 shots\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Counts:\\\", counts)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Verify three-qubit entanglement: only all-zeros and all-ones appear.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"unexpected = {k for k in counts if k not in (\\\"000\\\", \\\"111\\\")}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if unexpected:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"⚠️  Unexpected states: {unexpected}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"else:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(\\\"✅ Only |000⟩ and |111⟩ observed — 3-qubit GHZ entanglement confirmed.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"19-sec4-header\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## 4  ·  Deutsch's Algorithm\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Deutsch's algorithm decides whether a boolean function $f:\\\\{0,1\\\\}\\\\to\\\\{0,1\\\\}$ is\\n\",\n",
    "    \"*constant* (same output for both inputs) or *balanced* (different outputs) using only\\n\",\n",
    "    \"a **single** quantum oracle query — versus two classical queries.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Measurement result:**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Qubit 0 = `0` → $f$ is **constant**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Qubit 0 = `1` → $f$ is **balanced**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The oracle used here implements **f(x) = x** (balanced).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```spinach\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Initialise ancilla to |1⟩\\n\",\n",
    "    \"q 1 -> X\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Equal superposition on both qubits\\n\",\n",
    "    \"[q 0, q 1] -> H\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Oracle: f(x) = x  →  CNOT with q0 as control\\n\",\n",
    "    \"q 1 -> CX(q 0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Interference + measure\\n\",\n",
    "    \"q 0 -> H | M\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"20-deutsch-circuit\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ── 4a. Spinach source ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"SPH_DEUTSCH = \\\"\\\\n\\\".join([\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"# Deutsch's algorithm\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"q 1 -> X\\\",           # ancilla |1⟩\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"[q 0, q 1] -> H\\\",    # Hadamard on both\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"q 1 -> CX(q 0)\\\",     # oracle: f(x) = x  (balanced)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"q 0 -> H | M\\\",       # interference + measure\\n\",\n",
    "    \"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Spinach source:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(textwrap.indent(SPH_DEUTSCH, \\\"  \\\"))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"tket_deutsch = to_tket_circuit(SPH_DEUTSCH)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\nPyTKET circuit:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"show_tket_circuit(tket_deutsch)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"21-deutsch-draw\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ── 4b. Qiskit circuit diagram ────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"qc_deutsch = to_qiskit_circuit(SPH_DEUTSCH)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"qc_deutsch.draw('mpl', style='iqp', fold=-1)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"22-deutsch-shots\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ── 4c. Shot simulation ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, counts = run_shots(qc_deutsch, shots=1024,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                        title=\\\"Deutsch's algorithm: 1024 shots\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Counts:\\\", counts)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"23-deutsch-interpret\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ── 4d. Interpret result ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Only the register-0 bit (qubit 0) encodes the answer.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Qiskit classical register ordering: rightmost bit = qubit 0.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"q0_bits = {state[-1]: n for state, n in counts.items()}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"dominant = max(q0_bits, key=q0_bits.get)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if dominant == \\\"1\\\":\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    verdict = \\\"BALANCED  (f(0) ≠ f(1))\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"else:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    verdict = \\\"CONSTANT  (f(0) = f(1))\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Qubit-0 measurement:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for bit, n in sorted(q0_bits.items()):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    bar = \\\"█\\\" * int(40 * n / sum(q0_bits.values()))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"  |{bit}⟩  {bar} {n}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\n🔬 Deutsch's verdict: function is {verdict}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"   Expected: BALANCED (oracle = f(x) = x)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"assert dominant == \\\"1\\\", \\\"Deutsch algorithm gave wrong answer!\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"✅ Correct.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"24-summary\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Summary\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook demonstrated SpinachLang's end-to-end pipeline:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Write** compact quantum programs in the Spinach DSL (`.sph` syntax).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Compile** to a PyTKET `Circuit` with `to_tket_circuit()` — TKET's intermediate\\n\",\n",
    "    \"   representation enables backend-agnostic optimisation.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Convert** to a Qiskit `QuantumCircuit` with `to_qiskit_circuit()` (one call,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"   zero boilerplate), giving access to the full IBM Quantum ecosystem.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Simulate** locally with `qiskit_aer.AerSimulator` and visualise results\\n\",\n",
    "    \"   with Qiskit's built-in plotting tools.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Going further\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Goal | Code |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"|------|------|\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Run on real IBM hardware | `from qiskit_ibm_runtime import QiskitRuntimeService` |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Export to OpenQASM 2.0 | `spinachlang.compile_code(sph, \\\"qasm\\\")` |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Export to Cirq / Quil / Braket | `spinachlang.to_cirq_circuit(sph)` etc. |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Noise-model simulation | `AerSimulator.from_backend(noise_model)` |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Circuit optimisation | `pytket.passes.FullPeepholeOptimise().apply(tket_circuit)` |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"See the [SpinachLang repository](https://github.com/spinachlang/spinachlang) and\\n\",\n",
    "    \"the [PyTKET docs](https://cqcl.github.io/tket/pytket/api/) for more.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ]\n",
    "}\n"
